  "levi — Levi is the tribe serving in the Temple; today leviim are often called to the Torah after kohanim. Many carry the family name Levi or related traditions. Kohanim and leviim have other halachot (priestly blessing, tumah). If unsure of your status, ask family and your rav.": "леви — племя Храма; сегодня левиим читают Тору после коhаним. Другие галахот: биркат hа-коhаним, тума. Спросите семью и рава.",
